title: Welsh Assembly elections : turnout rates 1999 to 2011
summary: According to the Dutch business registry , the Welsh Assembly gained around 600 new small and medium enterprises between early 2003 and early 2011 .

The source defined SME ( or mkb , a Dutch abbreviation of midden- en kleinbedrijf ) as a company having between two to 249 employees , as well companies with one employee that are not classified as a freelancer/self-employed person .
